- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely because the paper applies the algorithm to the construction of matchbound certificates for proving termination of string rewriting, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possibility because the paper deals with the construction of certificates for proving termination, which can be seen as a logical problem. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possibility because the paper deals with the construction of certificates for proving termination, which is a topic that can be relevant to programming language design and analysis. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is a possibility because the paper deals with the manipulation of symbolic expressions (edge labels from a semiring) in the context of graph algorithms.
